    "title": "Scheuren Announces Funding Secured for Career and Technical Education Programs",
    "url": "http://www.RepScheuren.com/News/38050/Press-Releases/Scheuren-Announces-Funding-Secured-for-Career-and-Technical-Education-Programs",
    "date": null,
    "raw_text": "Scheuren Announces Funding Secured for Career and Technical Education Programs\nJune 3, 2026\nHARRISBURG – Rep. Donna Scheuren (R-Montgomery) announced today that two career and technical education (CTE) schools in the 147th Legislative District will be receiving grants from the Competitive Equipment Grants Program, through the Pennsylvania Department of Education (PDE).\nNorth Montco Technical Career Center and Western Montgomery Career and Technology Center each will receive $85,000, the maximum amount available, to update or purchase equipment for training of students in approved career and technical education programs.\n“At a time when technical and skilled trades jobs are in short supply, investing in high quality training programs is essential,” Scheuren said. “This funding strengthens hands on learning opportunities and helps ensure a strong, well prepared workforce for the future.”\nTo qualify for funding, school districts and career and technical centers must have eight or more PDE-approved CTE programs.\n“Let’s continue to champion and invest in career and technical education so every student has the tools and opportunities they need to succeed,” Scheuren concluded.\nRepresentative Donna Scheuren\n147th Legislative District\nPennsylvania House of Representatives\nMedia Contact: Melissa Fox\nmefox@pahousegop.com\nRepScheuren.com / Facebook.com/RepScheuren/\nShare\nSign Up to Receive Legislative Email Updates\nKeep up-to-date on the latest legislative and community news. Your email address will be used strictly for legislative purposes.\nEmail*\nZIP Code\nSubscribe",
    "ai_summary": {
      "summary": "Two career and technical education centers in Rep. Scheuren's district — North Montco Technical Career Center and Western Montgomery Career and Technology Center — will each receive $85,000 in state grants through the Pennsylvania Department of Education's Competitive Equipment Grants Program to purchase or update training equipment. The grants are administered by PDE and awarded to qualifying schools with eight or more approved CTE programs. Scheuren announced the funding but did not originate the grant program.",
      "action_type": "statement",
      "topics": [
